1
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:41,100
[Episode 07: Does death mean the end?]

2
00:00:41,100 --> 00:00:46,020
Be quiet, punk! Where do you think you are! Don't play innocent!

3
00:00:46,020 --> 00:00:48,290
- Hey!
- What's going on?
- Hey! Hey!

4
00:00:48,290 --> 00:00:50,810
Hey! You bastard! Hey!

5
00:00:50,810 --> 00:00:52,430
Let me go!

6
00:00:52,430 --> 00:00:54,380
If you were better, you could have hit me.

7
00:00:54,380 --> 00:00:56,000
What? What?

8
00:00:56,000 --> 00:01:00,150
Why don't you hit me and let me get some compensation money so I can live a comfortable life?

9
00:01:00,150 --> 00:01:01,950
Whoever that woman is,

10
00:01:01,950 --> 00:01:06,340
the one who reported me, I'm going to kill her if I get her–!

11
00:01:08,530 --> 00:01:10,160
What the–

12
00:01:11,750 --> 00:01:15,520
Say it again. What did you say?

13
00:01:16,220 --> 00:01:18,900
- What did you say?
- Mr. Jin, no!

14
00:01:18,900 --> 00:01:20,800
Don't do it!

15
00:01:23,350 --> 00:01:25,130
I should've...

16
00:01:25,740 --> 00:01:28,310
killed her then.

17
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:54,860
Please, don't do anything. Please.

18
00:02:15,550 --> 00:02:18,940
Look at this fool.

19
00:02:19,570 --> 00:02:22,880
You all saw that, right? I will never settle!

20
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:25,910
Since the camera is filming this, you guys figure it out. Call the police–

21
00:02:25,910 --> 00:02:28,810
Jang Jin Gu! Shut up!

22
00:02:30,880 --> 00:02:34,090
I'm telling you clearly, but every time you say something,

23
00:02:34,090 --> 00:02:36,240
your sentence will increase by that much.

24
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:40,000
- But that damn–
- Armed robbery is three and a half years to seven years!

25
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,480
And you were released from prison last year, right?

26
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:48,630
A person who was punished for armed robbery and committed a second offense within three years gets ten years or life imprisonment.

27
00:02:48,630 --> 00:02:52,870
The crime scene was clearly captured by your favorite camera. Footprints, fingerprints, and DNA.

28
00:02:52,870 --> 00:02:54,930
The scene is full of evidence to put you in prison.

29
00:02:54,930 --> 00:02:58,120
Nevertheless, you know that my testimony as a victim is imperative, right?

30
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,900
I don't know if it's unfortunate or fortunate, but I know many doctors,

31
00:03:00,900 --> 00:03:04,240
and depending on your attitude from now on,

32
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:07,060
the content of the medical report is going to look very different.

33
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:09,640
I'm saying it again in case you don't understand,

34
00:03:09,640 --> 00:03:12,500
but depending on what I say,

35
00:03:12,500 --> 00:03:16,230
you may not be able to see sunlight for the rest of your life. Did you get it?

36
00:03:16,230 --> 00:03:18,710
- Yes, Miss.
- Sit.

37
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:23,310
Where's my money? There must be money left, right?

38
00:03:23,310 --> 00:03:25,130
T-That-

39
00:03:25,130 --> 00:03:27,510
No way. Did you use all of that?

40
00:03:28,480 --> 00:03:32,730
If the detective came in even a minute later...

41
00:03:32,730 --> 00:03:37,020
The next card was a "palgwang" card! You saw the "samgwang" card I had, right?
(Playing cards called Hwatu, to play games such as GoStop.)

42
00:03:37,020 --> 00:03:39,840
Put those two together and it's a perfect "sampalgwang"!

43
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:43,550
That's art, right there!

44
00:03:43,550 --> 00:03:47,570
Do you know how much money that was?

45
00:03:47,570 --> 00:03:50,240
You gambled with our employees' salaries?

46
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:54,180
You little...! Let me go!

47
00:03:59,900 --> 00:04:00,950
[Episode 7]

48
00:04:00,950 --> 00:04:04,730
No matter how angry, you shouldn't do that at a place like this.

49
00:04:04,730 --> 00:04:06,690
If you're unlucky, he'll charge you with assault

50
00:04:06,690 --> 00:04:10,530
and file a complaint with the National Human Rights Commission of Korea. That will be troublesome for you later.

51
00:04:10,530 --> 00:04:12,830
I'm sorry.

52
00:04:12,830 --> 00:04:16,240
This goes for you and your boyfriend earlier,

53
00:04:16,240 --> 00:04:18,590
go calm down your temper.

54
00:04:18,590 --> 00:04:20,880
Boyfriend?

55
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:24,060
The flying kick guy.

56
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:26,900
No, that's not my boyfriend.

57
00:04:26,900 --> 00:04:28,450
Then your brother?

58
00:04:28,450 --> 00:04:30,210
No.

59
00:04:30,210 --> 00:04:35,600
If he's not your boyfriend or brother, why did he do a flying kick in the middle of the police station?

60
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:39,330
You guys making all kinds of trouble.

61
00:04:39,330 --> 00:04:41,200
I'm sorry.

62
00:04:41,200 --> 00:04:44,390
Calm down your temper and go. Okay?

63
00:04:44,390 --> 00:04:46,420
All right.

64
00:04:46,420 --> 00:04:48,280
Take care.

65
00:04:57,260 --> 00:04:59,330
You were a police officer?

66
00:04:59,330 --> 00:05:02,230
It's nice to see you here.

67
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:06,880
What kind of relationship do you have?

68
00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:11,770
Is it a habit to ask questions cutting to the chase, or is it an occupational disease?

69
00:05:11,770 --> 00:05:13,850
What do you mean by relationship?

70
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:15,660
What's your relationship with Dali?

71
00:05:15,660 --> 00:05:17,490
Dali?

72
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:22,330
Of course, if they're famous, they're all our friends.

73
00:05:22,330 --> 00:05:26,610
That's true. Hyung Byung Hun, Hyung Woo Sung, and Hyung Bin, they are all my friends.
(T/N: All famous actors)

74
00:05:26,610 --> 00:05:31,320
I don't know when Son will be back. We need to eat together sometime.
(T/N: Referring to soccer player Son Heung Min.)

75
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:32,920
Aren't you going to tell me?

76
00:05:32,920 --> 00:05:35,510
Are you serious?

77
00:05:35,510 --> 00:05:39,210
Ms. Kim Dali. She's not the type of person you can talk about carelessly!

78
00:05:39,210 --> 00:05:40,990
Won Tak.

79
00:05:43,500 --> 00:05:45,210
You came? Are you done?

80
00:05:45,210 --> 00:05:46,710
Yes.

81
00:05:47,490 --> 00:05:51,340
Mr. Jin, how do you know our Won Tak?

82
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:55,030
Our?

83
00:05:55,030 --> 00:05:56,940
Our Won Tak?

84
00:05:57,920 --> 00:05:59,860
Did you two know each other?

85
00:05:59,860 --> 00:06:01,480
I don't know him.

86
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:04,230
- The house I live in—
- He's a tenant.

87
00:06:04,230 --> 00:06:07,410
He lives in my rooftop room, and I'm the landlord.

88
00:06:08,700 --> 00:06:13,060
- But weren't you living alone? Do you live with someone?
- Whether I live alone or with someone, what's it to you?

89
00:06:13,060 --> 00:06:15,040
That's because...

90
00:06:17,010 --> 00:06:20,930
my upstairs neighbor was being so loud.

91
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:28,320
They say that noise between apartments is a serious issue these days. I heard that there are several people who have no consideration for community life.

92
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:35,430
- I told you. The landlord downstairs is crazy–
- Why do you have this on your face? It's messy.

93
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:38,440
I see. Won Tak is the tenant of your house.

94
00:06:38,440 --> 00:06:43,950
Please take good care of him. He's so energetic. Is there any noise between floors?

95
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:46,780
I told you there is. So I can't even sleep.

96
00:06:46,780 --> 00:06:50,520
What a load of crap. That's because the house was a mess—

97
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:53,150
He says he's sorry, and next time he'll be more careful.

98
00:06:53,150 --> 00:06:55,720
- When did I say that?
- We are done introducing ourselves, right?

99
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,880
We should go now.

100
00:06:59,310 --> 00:07:03,870
Mr. Jin, you did a great job too. Get home safely.

101
00:07:03,870 --> 00:07:05,980
What's wrong with you? Who is that jerk?

102
00:07:05,980 --> 00:07:10,980
Be quiet. I'll tell you everything when we get home. For the time being it's a secret that I live with you.

103
00:07:10,980 --> 00:07:13,280
- You living with me–
- I said be quiet.

104
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:15,310
Where are you going?

105
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:21,620
- Excuse me?
- Aren't you going to the art museum?

106
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:27,140
Are you not going to have the exhibition? There must be a lot of things to deal with!

107
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:29,680
Oh, right.

108
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:33,450
It was nice to see you, Won Tak. I should get going.

109
00:07:33,450 --> 00:07:37,350
I don't know where you live, but until the day we meet again, watch your mouth–

110
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:40,730
be careful of the noise between the floors.

111
00:07:40,730 --> 00:07:42,290
What?

112
00:07:42,910 --> 00:07:44,930
Hey, Dal–

113
00:07:57,940 --> 00:08:01,900
What is your relationship with "our" Won Tak?

114
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:05,070
- What?
- I don't think you guys have an ordinary relationship.

115
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:10,840
It is not an ordinary relationship, but it's a bit long to explain.

116
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:16,510
I guess it's a relationship involving more than three thousand eons? Is it about five thousand?

117
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:19,700
- Six thousand? Seven thousand?
- Well...

118
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:22,630
"Our" Won Tak is a really good and nice person.

119
00:08:22,630 --> 00:08:26,460
He's really righteous, law-abiding, professional, a man of rank,

120
00:08:26,460 --> 00:08:31,070
and above all, he's a detective in the violent crimes unit, so thieves can't even come close.

121
00:08:31,070 --> 00:08:35,400
It's like having a security company without paying.

122
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:39,430
He is also good at fighting. How reliable it is to be with him.

123
00:08:40,420 --> 00:08:42,360
Did you hire a bodyguard?

124
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:47,110
I mean, there's no one like him as a tenant.

125
00:08:47,110 --> 00:08:52,830
He is often on duty and has a lot of work, so he's so easy-going that he doesn't even wash up.

126
00:08:52,830 --> 00:08:56,810
So, how great is that? Electricity and water bills aren't that expensive.

127
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:59,650
Whoever heard that will think that you guys live together.

128
00:08:59,650 --> 00:09:01,100
What?

129
00:09:05,900 --> 00:09:09,180
Mr. Jin, how can you be that good at making jokes.

130
00:09:14,430 --> 00:09:17,320
I'll also talk to Won Tak about the noise between the floors–

131
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:22,200
All right. I will take care of the tenant,

132
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:27,310
so can we stop talking about "our" Won Tak? My ears are about to bleed.

133
00:09:27,310 --> 00:09:29,310
I'm sorry.

134
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:35,010
Is your hand okay?

135
00:09:36,340 --> 00:09:38,520
It's nothing.

136
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:42,480
I was going to give that jerk a good punch,

137
00:09:43,440 --> 00:09:47,010
- but you hugged me from behind.
- What?

138
00:09:47,010 --> 00:09:50,580
I was surprised, and in front of a lot of people too.

139
00:09:50,580 --> 00:09:54,570
I didn't hug you, but I was trying to stop you. I was afraid things would get worse.

140
00:09:56,680 --> 00:09:59,310
You stopped me so passionately.

141
00:09:59,310 --> 00:10:03,030
You should have gone as you were going. Why did you come back and cause a misunderstanding?

142
00:10:03,030 --> 00:10:05,250
That's because—

143
00:10:06,770 --> 00:10:08,610
That's because—

144
00:10:10,230 --> 00:10:14,470
G-Gukbap. I was going to ask about the gukbap restaurant.
(T/N: Rice and soup meal)

145
00:10:14,470 --> 00:10:16,620
- What?
- Usually, near police stations...

146
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:19,870
gukbap restaurants are famous.

147
00:10:19,870 --> 00:10:25,270
I went to do research on famous restaurants. You didn't think I went because I was worried about you, did you?

148
00:10:28,420 --> 00:10:31,830
And even if you're inside a police station,

149
00:10:31,830 --> 00:10:34,230
you can't do what you did earlier.

150
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:36,860
Do you know how tough those kinds of guys are?

151
00:10:36,860 --> 00:10:39,540
- I know well.
- What?

152
00:10:39,540 --> 00:10:43,170
I know it's hard to imagine because he's so cool now,

153
00:10:43,170 --> 00:10:45,880
but when Won Tak caused a lot of trouble,

154
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:48,380
my dad and I went to the police station a lot.

155
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:50,790
Again with that guy, "Our Won Tak"...

156
00:10:50,790 --> 00:10:53,850
I've met all kinds of criminals,

157
00:10:53,850 --> 00:10:56,680
from pickpocketers to gangster bosses, back then.

158
00:10:56,680 --> 00:11:00,380
I probably know more about them than you, Mr. Jin.

159
00:11:02,710 --> 00:11:07,670
Aren't you making light of my progress just because I am handsome?

160
00:11:07,670 --> 00:11:11,240
Don't you remember the tiger tattoo covering my body?

161
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:16,000
- Even if I look like this, I'm still the famous street fight of the Majang neighborhood–
- Wasn't that a sticker?

162
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,710
Who said that?

163
00:11:17,710 --> 00:11:22,780
When I saw it back then, the tiger was missing a few teeth and some of its claws had been erased.

164
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:31,500
And don't you remember, in the Netherlands when the power–

165
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:35,670
♫ The sun is embracing you ♫

166
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:37,800
...when the power went out?

167
00:11:38,490 --> 00:11:43,060
♫ Show me when I open the window ♫

168
00:11:43,060 --> 00:11:46,190
♫ The rain has stopped ♫

169
00:11:46,190 --> 00:11:49,590
♫ It's the moment I've been waiting for ♫

170
00:11:49,590 --> 00:11:55,160
I thought you said you had forgotten it all. But it seems you remember stuff like that clearly.

171
00:11:56,010 --> 00:11:59,210
Of course not, how could you forget it?

172
00:11:59,210 --> 00:12:02,320
I am a walking sculpture.

173
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,900
Sculpture?

174
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:07,480
What does that laugh mean?

175
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:08,920
But I did not laugh.

176
00:12:08,920 --> 00:12:11,760
I definitely heard you laugh.

177
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:14,070
It must be your imagination.

178
00:12:14,070 --> 00:12:18,960
♫ One step closer, two steps closer ♫

179
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:21,830
♫ Will you come closer and hug me? ♫

180
00:12:21,830 --> 00:12:23,960
You said sculpture!

181
00:12:27,170 --> 00:12:29,830
Scul—

182
00:12:29,830 --> 00:12:33,920
You are definitely no sculpture.

183
00:12:35,980 --> 00:12:38,770
Sculpture...

184
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:42,580
Aren't you laughing a bit too much?

185
00:12:42,580 --> 00:12:44,990
I am sorry.

186
00:12:44,990 --> 00:12:46,340
[Certificate of registration (including deletions) - Multi-owned Building]

187
00:12:46,340 --> 00:12:49,110
[Matters concerning management other than possession]

188
00:12:49,110 --> 00:12:51,430
[Jang Tae Jin]

189
00:12:53,290 --> 00:12:56,010
[Dondon F&B organization chart]

190
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:57,630
[Director Jin Moo Hak]

191
00:12:59,070 --> 00:13:00,510
[Director Jin Moo Hak]

192
00:13:00,510 --> 00:13:02,680
He keeps bothering me.

193
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:05,200
It may have become a company right now,

194
00:13:05,200 --> 00:13:08,950
but they are just upstarts who started from nothing on the floors of the market.

195
00:13:08,950 --> 00:13:12,320
Both the father and the stepmother are the same.

196
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:16,830
They are pretty vulgar people who know nothing other than money.

197
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:21,300
You don't have to worry. He will go away once the debt is paid off.

198
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,350
What is the amount of debt owed to him?

199
00:13:24,350 --> 00:13:28,030
I heard it's a sum of two billion won.

200
00:13:28,030 --> 00:13:29,880
Two billion won.

201
00:13:31,410 --> 00:13:35,770
He dares to want Dali at that price?

202
00:13:35,770 --> 00:13:40,730
Even though he is ignorant, I don't think he is that stupid.

203
00:13:42,710 --> 00:13:47,620
This is none of your business, and we don't have that kind of relationship.

204
00:13:48,360 --> 00:13:50,880
Mr. Jin,

205
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:55,420
what are you doing? We have to pay.

206
00:14:17,110 --> 00:14:20,410
How did even money get involved between them

207
00:14:20,410 --> 00:14:24,160
and cause Dali to be like this?

208
00:14:24,160 --> 00:14:31,080
He acts all high and mighty but does not know how the world works.

209
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:35,900
Arrange a way for us to meet naturally.

210
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:39,310
You want to meet this guy?

211
00:14:44,180 --> 00:14:46,000
Thanks for your work.

212
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:51,100
There was a problem with the wiring that took time to resolve. We are running behind the schedule. I think we need to pull an all-nighter.

213
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:53,320
There won't be a problem with the catering, right?

214
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:57,020
Actually... the attendees are not confirmed yet...

215
00:14:57,020 --> 00:15:00,860
Did you not check the RSVP of VIPs yet?

216
00:15:00,860 --> 00:15:03,780
That is...

217
00:15:03,780 --> 00:15:05,650
Hello.

218
00:15:05,650 --> 00:15:09,770
Will Director Jang be attending the opening event?

219
00:15:10,860 --> 00:15:13,980
His schedule is not clear?

220
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:15,400
Sorry?

221
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:17,780
Minister Choi?

222
00:15:17,780 --> 00:15:22,670
I am calling to confirm if Minister Choi is attending the opening event tomorrow.

223
00:15:22,670 --> 00:15:27,870
He's not there yet? Then when can I confirm?

224
00:15:27,870 --> 00:15:31,290
Maybe it's because of the article last time. They are checking

225
00:15:31,290 --> 00:15:35,230
to see who else is coming and judging to see if they should come.

226
00:15:35,230 --> 00:15:38,640
It would be great if a magnate like Director Jang Tae Jin could change the wind here.

227
00:15:38,640 --> 00:15:42,260
But he happens to have an overseas business trip.

228
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:46,260
That is... what I meant was...

229
00:15:46,260 --> 00:15:51,110
Celebs talking about this kind of event will create articles about it, and that will draw people to this exhibition.

230
00:15:51,110 --> 00:15:55,310
Just go ahead with the preparations keeping the number of people we planned for, for now. We can't disrespect guests after inviting them.

231
00:15:55,310 --> 00:15:56,370
Yes, all right.

232
00:15:56,370 --> 00:15:58,330
- I said, move!
- My gosh!

233
00:15:58,330 --> 00:16:00,320
Mr. Kim! My gosh!

234
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,950
Seriously, why are you doing this?!

235
00:16:01,950 --> 00:16:03,780
I called dibs on this place first!

236
00:16:03,780 --> 00:16:05,130
What?

237
00:16:05,130 --> 00:16:08,790
You think you can get the place without an owner, just because you called dibs?

238
00:16:08,790 --> 00:16:11,520
- I said move!
- My gosh!

239
00:16:12,910 --> 00:16:16,270
What is the matter? This section is reserved for Ms. Hong Ja Young.

240
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:18,040
I heard that Ms. Hong withdrew?

241
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:21,530
- Withdrew, she didn't...
- Sweetie, can't I have this place?

242
00:16:21,530 --> 00:16:25,390
It's the main spot and you cannot just put up any work here.

243
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:27,820
Also, isn't the size of my work similar?

244
00:16:27,820 --> 00:16:29,220
The size?

245
00:16:29,220 --> 00:16:33,640
If the artwork doesn't have artistic performance is it still great just because it's big? It should be representative of the group exhibition!

246
00:16:33,640 --> 00:16:38,900
Isn't that why I am suggesting my artwork to be here? Going by its international reputation and quality.

247
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:43,180
Quality of the work? Did you say quality?

248
00:16:43,710 --> 00:16:47,000
Ms. Yang, how many times have you had a private exhibition?

249
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,800
Spending your own money to have an exhibition? Who is going to acknowledge that?

250
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:55,000
Then Mr. Kim, did you get invited to the Biennale art show this time?
(A famous art exhibition in Italy)

251
00:16:55,010 --> 00:16:57,520
- What?
- My goodnes. My goodness.

252
00:16:57,520 --> 00:17:02,580
- I guess you really didn't get an invitation. Oh my, he really didn't get invited.
- Everyone got invited...

253
00:17:02,580 --> 00:17:05,330
Will you two...

254
00:17:06,250 --> 00:17:08,100
really be all right?

255
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:09,490
Yes.

256
00:17:09,490 --> 00:17:13,580
It's not a problem for me to install your work here Mr. Kim,

257
00:17:13,580 --> 00:17:18,510
but your work will get camouflaged with the wall since it's a similar color.

258
00:17:18,510 --> 00:17:21,140
We can just paint there again.

259
00:17:21,140 --> 00:17:26,280
The opening is tomorrow. How are they going it repaint it? Then, how about putting mine here?

260
00:17:26,280 --> 00:17:33,840
I would like to install your work here Ms. Yang, but look at what's there beside it.

261
00:17:41,390 --> 00:17:44,350
We are good now, right?

262
00:17:44,350 --> 00:17:49,090
You are going to install it where it was meant for originally, right? I think that'll be good.

263
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:58,040
They are usually decent but they get a bit sensitive before exhibitions.

264
00:17:58,040 --> 00:18:01,460
Is Ms. Hong still not here?

265
00:18:01,460 --> 00:18:05,250
Curator Song has gone there for now. But seeing how she hasn't called...

266
00:18:05,250 --> 00:18:08,780
Isn't it time we look for an alternative now?

267
00:18:08,780 --> 00:18:11,240
Where is Ms. Hong's studio?

268
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:13,860
Studio?

269
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:31,180
Why did "garbage" come all the way here?

270
00:18:35,660 --> 00:18:37,760
[Dondon gamjatang]

271
00:18:39,980 --> 00:18:43,280
I am here to clean up my shit.

272
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:46,900
What sort of shit is that?

273
00:18:46,900 --> 00:18:51,080
- I.C.M.S.
- Say what?

274
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:55,940
I clean up my own shit. That's my belief.

275
00:18:55,940 --> 00:18:58,670
What a load of shit.

276
00:18:58,670 --> 00:19:02,510
What a load of shit, real—

277
00:19:06,080 --> 00:19:08,450
Director!

278
00:19:09,550 --> 00:19:15,740
What is this situation?

279
00:19:19,880 --> 00:19:24,520
She has to let me in first for me to go and propose something.

280
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:29,430
I waited three hours in front of the studio. I came out for a bit.

281
00:19:29,430 --> 00:19:33,090
I thought about it, and I came empty-handed.

282
00:19:33,090 --> 00:19:36,400
I am trying to, at least, buy some fruits to give her.

283
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:40,380
What? You are coming here right now?

284
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:46,620
We have to resolve this within two hours. We don't have time and no other alternative.

285
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:48,170
All right.

286
00:20:02,450 --> 00:20:07,990
Actually, there is another reason that she got so angry.

287
00:20:07,990 --> 00:20:10,720
"The living and the dead" number 1

288
00:20:10,720 --> 00:20:15,670
is a work she designed thinking of her late mother.

289
00:20:15,670 --> 00:20:20,220
That ignorant guy kept ranting about that kind of work.

290
00:20:20,220 --> 00:20:23,540
And called it "shit" and "garbage".

291
00:20:34,250 --> 00:20:40,050
Wow, you guys are so annoying and troublesome.

292
00:20:41,860 --> 00:20:44,810
Ms. Hong.

293
00:20:44,810 --> 00:20:47,050
About the accident that happened in the morning–

294
00:20:47,050 --> 00:20:52,690
You are sorry, apologetic, and cannot apologize enough?

295
00:20:52,690 --> 00:20:56,670
I know all that. So, let's just cut to the chase.

296
00:20:56,670 --> 00:20:58,680
What did you bring me, dear?

297
00:20:58,680 --> 00:21:00,220
Sorry?

298
00:21:00,220 --> 00:21:06,390
That huge ruckus took place after you were appointed the new director.

299
00:21:06,390 --> 00:21:10,450
You must not have come empty-handed, right?

300
00:21:10,450 --> 00:21:14,550
I am curious as to what

301
00:21:14,550 --> 00:21:16,600
you brought me.

302
00:21:18,580 --> 00:21:22,150
We will compensate you very well for the damaged artwork—

303
00:21:22,150 --> 00:21:25,170
The insurance company will take care of that.

304
00:21:26,570 --> 00:21:31,830
If you're interested... the Hamilton Foundation in New York is offering a residency—

305
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:36,860
I don't know if it will be possible because my schedule is completely full until next year.

306
00:21:38,980 --> 00:21:42,770
I see...

307
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:47,220
Then, what about a private exhibition?

308
00:21:47,220 --> 00:21:51,940
We'll go straight into showing your private exhibition once our current one is over.

309
00:21:51,940 --> 00:21:56,090
It may not be immediate, but we'll purchase your artwork,

310
00:21:56,090 --> 00:21:59,590
and we'll use the best material for the art brochure—

311
00:22:01,060 --> 00:22:03,450
Is there even a future for Cheongsong?

312
00:22:03,450 --> 00:22:07,710
I was thinking the current exhibition was the last one.

313
00:22:08,590 --> 00:22:14,100
- Ms. Hong.
- I'll make sure you get a private exhibition within one year.

314
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:18,350
If you'll give us your permission, we'll have one next year, and the next...

315
00:22:18,350 --> 00:22:23,730
I want to personally work on holding an exhibition with you at our art museum.

316
00:22:25,450 --> 00:22:27,750
I saw somewhere

317
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:31,420
that people will get down on their knees in situations like these, too.

318
00:22:32,870 --> 00:22:37,630
I guess you're too much of a snobby elite to do that.

319
00:22:37,630 --> 00:22:42,930
- Ms. Hong!
- Will you give your permission... if I kneel?

320
00:22:42,930 --> 00:22:46,310
Giving a condition is a negotiation, not a favor.

321
00:22:46,310 --> 00:22:49,700
You normally hate stuff like this.

322
00:22:49,700 --> 00:22:52,020
Why are you being like this, Ms. Hong?

323
00:22:52,020 --> 00:22:56,400
If kneeling will make you forgive us, I'll happily do so.

324
00:22:56,400 --> 00:23:00,560
I truly apologize for what happened today.

325
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:03,050
Please, don't do this Director.

326
00:23:03,050 --> 00:23:05,940
- Please, Ms. Hong.
- Oh, forget it.

327
00:23:05,940 --> 00:23:08,680
Why can't you take a joke?

328
00:23:08,680 --> 00:23:12,530
Oh, it must have arrived by now.

329
00:23:16,010 --> 00:23:20,050
What kind of magic did you use that made Ms. Hong change her mind?

330
00:23:20,050 --> 00:23:22,650
It's amazing!

331
00:23:22,650 --> 00:23:24,650
Be careful, please.

332
00:23:24,650 --> 00:23:29,050
Up there.

333
00:23:31,420 --> 00:23:34,710
Oh!

334
00:23:40,190 --> 00:23:44,270
I'll carry it myself, sir.

335
00:23:44,270 --> 00:23:48,870
No, it's nothing. It's fine.

336
00:23:50,700 --> 00:23:54,980
What's he doing?

337
00:23:58,450 --> 00:24:04,180
He said, "The Living and The Dead 3" has arrived.

338
00:24:06,310 --> 00:24:10,680
- You're not going to go?
- Thank you so much, Ms. Hong.

339
00:24:10,680 --> 00:24:12,790
I didn't do it to be thanked.

340
00:24:12,790 --> 00:24:16,880
I did it because it'll be a loss to us artists if Cheongsong closes down.

341
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:21,240
This is why you have to keep your promise about what you said just now.

342
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:26,470
Your promise that Cheongsong will continue to hold private exhibitions of my work,

343
00:24:26,470 --> 00:24:29,470
next year, the year after that, and onwards.

344
00:24:29,470 --> 00:24:32,180
It'll be our honor.

345
00:24:33,260 --> 00:24:38,060
Ms. Hong! You're the best.

346
00:24:38,060 --> 00:24:40,750
Oh, my, my! Let's hurry up.

347
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:46,220
Twenty-four hours isn't enough to set everything up before the opening.

348
00:24:46,220 --> 00:24:51,930
Oh, right! What does the piece of trash from this morning do?

349
00:24:55,740 --> 00:24:59,060
He made a mistake due to his ignorance in this field, but he's not a bad person.

350
00:24:59,060 --> 00:25:03,150
On the contrary, he's someone that Cheongsong has to thank a lot for.

351
00:25:03,150 --> 00:25:08,050
How funny. I asked what his occupation is,

352
00:25:08,050 --> 00:25:12,480
not if he's a good person.

353
00:25:12,480 --> 00:25:19,510
The harmony of the disharmonious... How intriguing.

354
00:25:27,380 --> 00:25:29,120
Oh, my!

355
00:25:39,080 --> 00:25:43,200
Hello, I'm Dondon F&B Director Jin Moo Hak's executive secretary.

356
00:25:44,610 --> 00:25:46,510
You said... who?

357
00:25:47,660 --> 00:25:50,590
Jang Tae Jin?

358
00:25:50,590 --> 00:25:55,750
He said he'll meet with you whenever you have time.

359
00:25:55,750 --> 00:25:58,020
Meet with me?

360
00:25:58,020 --> 00:26:02,700
He said he wants to talk about Cheongsong's debt. My prediction was correct, don't you think?

361
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:05,200
What did you predict?

362
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,400
I told you last time.

363
00:26:07,400 --> 00:26:10,650
How I think Century Group will pay you back.

364
00:26:10,650 --> 00:26:12,420
Why would he?

365
00:26:12,420 --> 00:26:14,820
He's head over heels!

366
00:26:14,820 --> 00:26:19,140
He's going to flex with his money. Two billion is nothing for Century Group.

367
00:26:19,140 --> 00:26:23,610
With his biggest roadblock, Director Kim Nak Chun gone,

368
00:26:23,610 --> 00:26:27,890
it'll be a piece of cake and we won't have to worry about anything either.

369
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:31,890
Isn't it great news? When would you like to meet him?

370
00:26:31,890 --> 00:26:35,580
The sooner the better, right? Like, tonight?

371
00:26:35,580 --> 00:26:39,320
- I'm busy!
- Then, what about tomorrow night?

372
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:41,320
I'm busy tomorrow, too!

373
00:26:41,320 --> 00:26:43,880
- Then, what about the day after tomorrow?
- I said I'm busy!

374
00:26:43,880 --> 00:26:46,400
I have no time to meet that punk!

375
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:51,390
Also, if he wants to meet, tell him to come to me! How dare he order me around to come and go?

376
00:26:51,390 --> 00:26:53,500
I have money too!

377
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:58,020
Still... This is a rare opportunity...

378
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:03,560
Understood, sir.

379
00:27:06,510 --> 00:27:08,290
What's this?

380
00:27:08,290 --> 00:27:14,300
It's from Ms. Hong's "The Living and The Dead" collection that you purchased, artwork Number 1.

381
00:27:33,330 --> 00:27:35,120
Peek-a-boo

382
00:27:39,300 --> 00:27:41,410
This is it? A keychain?

383
00:27:41,410 --> 00:27:46,620
She said that the explanation of the piece, the process, and everything is in there.

384
00:27:46,620 --> 00:27:50,960
She also said that, without your permission,

385
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:56,420
no one can show it in an exhibition, print it, or shoot it anywhere.

386
00:27:56,420 --> 00:28:00,010
It means, now you're a collector, too.

387
00:28:10,790 --> 00:28:12,460
Are you going to throw it away?

388
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:22,470
It's so expensive though.

389
00:28:24,080 --> 00:28:33,790
I... I bought a piece of trash for one hundred million won!!

390
00:28:37,580 --> 00:28:39,250
What's wrong with him?

391
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:45,470
You got a call. Aren't you going to pick it up?

392
00:28:45,470 --> 00:28:50,430
- Who is it?
- 3,000 worth.

393
00:28:50,430 --> 00:28:53,960
Oh, that's not right. 3,000 eons. Eons!

394
00:29:03,640 --> 00:29:05,550
Jin Moo Hak speaking.

395
00:29:11,650 --> 00:29:13,480
Leave it here!

396
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:18,330
I wanted to let you know that fortunately, the issue has been resolved. You must have been really worried.

397
00:29:18,330 --> 00:29:21,290
Oh, yes. Well, yes...

398
00:29:21,290 --> 00:29:24,630
You probably have a lot of other things to worry about. You didn't have to worry about me.

399
00:29:24,630 --> 00:29:27,770
That makes me worried...

400
00:29:27,770 --> 00:29:31,140
This shouldn't be here.

401
00:29:31,140 --> 00:29:35,060
Good job. It's a little late but I'm sorry.

402
00:29:35,060 --> 00:29:38,250
Will you be at the opening ceremony tomorrow?

403
00:29:38,250 --> 00:29:45,130
I'll be there! I'll go even if it's the apocalypse, so wait for me.

404
00:29:51,560 --> 00:29:57,030
I don't know what happened. I thought she would never change her mind back.

405
00:29:57,030 --> 00:30:01,790
Oh, right. Do you think Ms. Hong will do the opening performance herself?

406
00:30:01,790 --> 00:30:04,510
She probably will. There's not much time to find someone to do it.

