744
00:55:01,990 --> 00:55:06,880
The truth is, the thought of going in the coffin was uncomfortable.

745
00:55:08,520 --> 00:55:13,180
It's cold, dark,

746
00:55:13,180 --> 00:55:16,550
damp, and scary.

747
00:55:16,550 --> 00:55:20,900
But when I actually laid down,

748
00:55:22,100 --> 00:55:26,370
it was warm, soft,

749
00:55:26,370 --> 00:55:28,510
and cozy.

750
00:55:30,030 --> 00:55:33,190
I don't know if you sprayed perfume, but it smelled good.

751
00:55:35,250 --> 00:55:40,300
Should I say that it put my mind at ease?

752
00:55:44,770 --> 00:55:47,010
It comforted me.

753
00:55:53,150 --> 00:55:56,350
My mom died on a particularly cold day.

754
00:56:07,680 --> 00:56:09,670
I'm being thoughtless.

755
00:56:11,540 --> 00:56:15,850
Doing this in front of someone who was mourning not long ago... I'm sorry.

756
00:56:18,010 --> 00:56:22,830
Can I ask how old you were when she passed away?

757
00:56:22,830 --> 00:56:28,080
It's not some kind of big secret. She died when I was ten years old.

758
00:56:29,520 --> 00:56:31,800
You must have been heartbroken.

759
00:56:33,530 --> 00:56:38,150
If she could see that you grew up so wonderful like this, she would be happy.

760
00:56:39,750 --> 00:56:41,590
No.

761
00:56:42,670 --> 00:56:45,300
I hope that doesn't happen.

762
00:56:47,370 --> 00:56:54,030
People say that, because they have a soul, they will watch over you,

763
00:56:54,030 --> 00:57:00,860
become stars and protect you, and say that we will meet again someday,

764
00:57:03,200 --> 00:57:06,090
but I wish death was the end.

765
00:57:07,570 --> 00:57:12,510
Just as it means, the end. Just the end.

766
00:57:14,490 --> 00:57:16,620
That's what I hope.

767
00:57:20,760 --> 00:57:22,710
My mom...

768
00:57:25,010 --> 00:57:27,500
was really sick.

769
00:57:31,750 --> 00:57:34,680
She suffered throughout her life

770
00:57:39,230 --> 00:57:44,080
and I remember her being sick every day.

771
00:57:47,350 --> 00:57:49,500
Her body ached

772
00:57:52,540 --> 00:57:57,910
and her heart ached because I would be growing up without a mother.

773
00:58:01,100 --> 00:58:05,000
The strawberries are washed.

774
00:58:11,710 --> 00:58:14,290
Eat this.

775
00:58:14,290 --> 00:58:16,450
Come on, eat it.

776
00:58:18,790 --> 00:58:22,220
Did you eat?

777
00:58:22,220 --> 00:58:24,370
Yes.

778
00:58:24,370 --> 00:58:27,090
Don't go skipping meals. Okay?

779
00:58:28,780 --> 00:58:34,030
You have to make sure to eat even if I'm not here.

780
00:58:34,030 --> 00:58:36,140
Okay?

781
00:58:48,190 --> 00:58:50,040
Eat.

782
00:59:10,240 --> 00:59:12,510
Of all days,

783
00:59:14,550 --> 00:59:17,580
why did she have to die on the coldest day?

784
00:59:19,730 --> 00:59:22,030
The ground was frozen

785
00:59:23,680 --> 00:59:26,150
while burying her coffin,

786
00:59:27,240 --> 00:59:30,320
so the workers cursed so much...

787
00:59:33,960 --> 00:59:37,860
How can a person's life be without even a ray of sunshine?

788
00:59:48,590 --> 00:59:51,280
It should have been enough that she suffered that much.

789
00:59:52,200 --> 00:59:55,330
Why should she have to worry about me after she passes?

790
00:59:58,490 --> 01:00:00,460
Let's go now.

791
01:00:07,500 --> 01:00:10,440
I'm sure she was watching over you,

792
01:00:10,440 --> 01:00:12,690
all this time, growing up.

793
01:00:15,040 --> 01:00:20,920
Without missing a single moment, cheering and worrying.

794
01:00:22,220 --> 01:00:27,680
She would be happy that you grew up to be this wonderful

795
01:00:29,010 --> 01:00:30,310
and without going down the wrong path.

796
01:00:30,310 --> 01:00:34,130
♫ Come close to me ♫

797
01:00:35,420 --> 01:00:41,590
♫ Stay by my side with love ♫

798
01:00:43,030 --> 01:00:48,750
♫ Everything in the world is ♫

799
01:00:48,750 --> 01:00:53,760
♫ Beautifully colored in pink ♫

800
01:00:53,760 --> 01:00:57,840
♫ This feeling is getting deeper ♫

801
01:00:57,840 --> 01:01:05,280
♫ It's strange how we met ♫

802
01:01:05,280 --> 01:01:12,580
♫ How did I fall in love at first sight? ♫

803
01:01:12,580 --> 01:01:16,770
♫ It must be a fate ♫

804
01:01:16,770 --> 01:01:20,250
♫ That is not easy to explain ♫

805
01:01:20,250 --> 01:01:29,510
♫ I'm the only one for you. I'll give you this love ♫

806
01:01:36,690 --> 01:01:43,960
♫ Like calm music, it keeps lingering ♫

807
01:01:43,960 --> 01:01:51,380
♫ I kept wanting to listen to your shy voice ♫

808
01:01:51,380 --> 01:01:57,260
♫ Do you know how anxious I feel? ♫

809
01:01:57,260 --> 01:02:00,110
♫ As if today is the last day... ♫

